<doc id="1117505" wikidata="Q1001614" url="?curid=1117505" title="Aix-en-Issart">
<text>Aix-en-Issart () is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in northern France. A place named &quot;in Ascio&quot; is mentioned as early as 800 AD while during the Middle Ages the place used to be called &quot;Rodenaken&quot; by Flemish speaking people.

==Geography==
A small village situated some 5 miles(7 km) east of Montreuil-sur-Mer, at the D149 and D129 crossroads, by the banks of the small river Bras de Bronne, a tributary of the Canche.

==Population==
==Notable person==
Jean de Beaurain (1696–1771), geographer, was born in Aix-en-Issart.

==See also==
*Communes of the Pas-de-Calais department

