<doc id="1117544" wikidata="Q1454304" url="?curid=1117544" title="Marshal of Poland">
<text>Marshal of Poland () is the highest rank in the Polish Army. It has been granted to only six officers. At present, Marshal is equivalent to a field marshal or general of the army (OF-10) in other NATO armies.

==History==

Today there are no living Marshals of Poland, since this rank is bestowed only on military commanders who have achieved victory in war. Recently, however, the rank of four-star with the modernised name &quot;Generał&quot; has been introduced, and on August 15, 2002, was granted to Czesław Piątas, at present civilian, former Chief of the General Staff of the Polish Armed Forces.

==List of Marshals==
In all, the following people have served as Marshals of Poland.
